==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crinoidea
<hw>Cri*noid"e*a</hw> <pr>(kr⟦isl⟧*noid"⟦esl⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.
pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr. <grk>kri`non</grk> lily + <ets>-oid</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>crino⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large
class of Echinodermata, including numerous extinct families and genera,
but comparatively few living ones. Most of the fossil species, like some
that are recent, were attached by a jointed stem. See
<er>Blastoidea</er>, <er>Cystoidea</er>, <er>Comatula</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crinoidean</ent>⟦br⟧
